parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spot welds on the firewall can cause the clutch pedal and brake pedal assembly to move laterally, leading to difficulty shifting gears, loss of braking power, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Creaking or popping noise when depressing the clutch pedal
lateral movement of the clutch pedal and brake pedal assembly
difficulty shifting gears
and loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal assembly can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal assembly can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Firewall Clutch Pedal Mounting Bracket Weld Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the welds on the clutch pedal mounting bracket on the firewall can cause the clutch pedal to become inoperable, leading to difficulty shifting gears, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Snapping or creaking sounds when the clutch pedal is depressed
the clutch pedal moves or sticks to the floor
the brake pedal moves when the clutch is depressed
difficulty shifting into gear
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Pedal Assembly Failure due to Spot Weld Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spot welds that hold the clutch pedal assembly to the firewall can cause the clutch pedal to move and squeak when engaged, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Squeaky clutch pedal
clutch pedal moves when engaged
difficulty shifting gears
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.
